# /arc-myproject — Example arc bootstrap

Loading the myproject cluster (rename this file to arc-<your-slug>.md) (project files, experiment registry,
roadmap, lab notebook, latest session handoff). The dump becomes one user
message → captured as cache prefix → 90% discount on subsequent turns for
the rest of the arc.

```!
${HOME}/.claude/state/scripts/arc-bootstrap.sh myproject
```

Now ground yourself in the loaded context. Note the active phase, latest
roadmap commitments,, and anything in the most recent session handoff that
constrains the next move. Then ask the user what to work on.

Arc cache pattern doc: `~/ai/global-graph/patterns/prompt-cache-arc-pattern.md`
Config: `~/.claude/state/arcs/myproject.conf` — edit to add/remove files
